-- French Stocks Gain; Cap Gemini, France Telecom, Ipsos Rise as Thales Drops
-- David Altaner
-- 2010-07-29T13:39:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/crit-edf-ipsos-mr-bricolage-thales-vallourec-french-equity-preview.html

          
          
             France’s  CAC 40 Index  rose 49.03, or
1.3 percent, to 3,719.39 at 3:38 p.m. in Paris. The  SBF-120
Index  climbed 1.2 percent.  
 The following stocks are among the most active in the
French equity market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses
after company names.  
 Cap Gemini SA  (CAP FP) rose 8.5 percent to 36.76 euros.
Europe’s biggest computer-services company raised its 2010
operating margin forecast to more than 6.5 percent, from a
previous range of between 6 percent and 6.5 percent.  
 France Telecom SA  (FTE FP) rose 6.3 percent to 16.13 euros.
The country’s biggest telephone operator said it will maintain
its annual dividend through 2012.  
 Ipsos SA  (IPS FP) gained 3.7 percent to 30.70 euros as the
market-research company said first-half net income rose to 23.4
million euros ($30.6 million) from 14.3 million euros.  
 Neurones  (NRO FP) rose 3.9 percent to 6.75 euros. The
computer-services company said first-half sales rose to 115.5
million euros from 107.7 million euros.  
 Thales SA  (HO FP) fell 2.2 percent to 26.35 euros even
after Europe’s biggest maker of defense electronics reported
increased first-half profit. Thales said difficulties providing
equipment for the Airbus A400M military plane and a maritime
patrol boat for Turkey could have a “material impact” on
results this year.  
